text.section:
A city, consolidated local government, or urban-county government may initiate proceedings to establish a management district upon receipt by the executive authority of a written petition requesting the formation of a management district. A petition requesting the formation of a management district shall contain:
The signatures and addresses of at least thirty-three percent (33%) of the owners of real property within the proposed management district and a number of real property owners, who together are the owners of real property equal to at least fifty-one percent (51%) of the assessed value of property within the proposed management district;
An accurate description of the boundaries of the proposed management district;
An economic improvement plan that shall provide:
A description of the economic improvements to be provided within the district;
A preliminary estimate of the annual costs of the proposed economic improvements;
The proposed method of assessing the costs of the economic improvements against the properties; and
The proposed makeup of the board of directors of the management district, its powers and duties.
